  "prompt": "How do I delete a Google+ profile without username and password?",
  "response": "As of April 2019, Google+ has been shut down for consumer accounts, and thus there is no longer a need to delete a Google+ profile. If you have an account linked to other Google services and want to manage your data, you can follow these general steps:\n\n1. **Go to Google Account Settings**: Visit [myaccount.google.com](https://myaccount.google.com).\n2. **Sign In**: If you're able to sign in using your Google account credentials (if you remember the password), do so.\n3. **Privacy & Personalization**: Look for the privacy and personalization options to manage your account settings.\n4. **Data & Personalization**: From there, you can manage your data and services linked to your account.\n\nIf you do not have access to the username or password for your Google account, you will need to recover your account first. Here\u2019s how you can do that:\n\n1. **Visit the Account Recovery Page**: Go to the [Google Account Recovery page](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery).\n2. **Enter Your Email**: Enter the email address associated with your account.\n3. **Follow the Prompts**: Google will guide you through steps to verify your identity and reset your password.\n\nIf you're unable to recover the account and Google+ is not an issue anymore, you may want to consider creating a new Google account, as Google+ is no longer operational.\n\nIf you have further questions or need help with a specific issue, feel free to ask!",
